com.camerontec.catalys.server.configuration

Class ConfigurationAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.configuration.ConfigurationAgent

  • public class ConfigurationAgent
extends Object
    This class is created by catalys and can be used to access the configuration of the Catalys server.

    Users can view and modify the configuration of the server, undo or apply their changes, persist changes, or reload the configuration from XML.

    Summary of the Configuration Agent API:

    1. Add methods: addXYZ where XYZ are any supported configuration element in CatalysConfig.dtd
    2. Get method: get the value of an attribute
    3. Set methods: to set a static attribute, custom attribute or property
    4. Undo method: Selectively cancel changes to the configuration domain
    5. Specialized methods:
      1. loadConfigurationFromXMLFile, persistConfigurationIntoXMLFile - load/save XML configuration.
      2. copySession - copy an existing session

    The configurationElementName parameter used in some of the addXYZ methods is equivalent to the XML element name of the desired configuration element.

    Author:
    mmattini and dplasto

        public Name copyTo(Name name,
                   String destinationName,
                   String descendantNamePattern,
                   String descendantNameReplacement)
        Copies an existing configuration object to the new one.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the configuration object to copy
        destinationName - the destination name
        descendantNamePattern - the regexp-formatted replacement pattern to use for renaming this node's descendants as part of the copy operation
        descendantNameReplacement - the regexp-formatted replacement expression to use for renaming this node's children as part of the copy operation
        Returns:
        Name of the new configuration object.
        Throws:
        ConfigurationChangeForbiddenException - if existing configuration is marked for delete, or it is Session or Application.

      • addTimerecord

        public Name addTimerecord(Name parentName,
                          String accumulatorClassName,
                          String id,
                          boolean inbound,
                          boolean fromStart)
        Add a TimeRecord configuration. Object will be added with default attributes
        Parameters:
        parentName - Name of parent in configuration model. Parent can be SessionManager, SouurceMessageProcessors, ListenerMessageProcessors or message processor (cannot be a selector, another Timestamp or Timerecord)
        accumulatorClassName - Class name to use for Timerecord (eg HistogramAccumulator)
        id - ID of time-record (we can have more than one)
        inbound - determines if inbound or outbound messages should be time-stamped. This is used only for an IMessageProcessor that implements both IFIXSource and IFIXListener
        fromStart - whether this is a from-start time record
        Returns:
        Name of time-record

        Returns a summary of the state of all configured sessions for a given application if 'name' is of type application) or the state of a single session if the type of the 'name' is session.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of top level node to get a summary for. This can be either an Application or Session node. If an Application node is in passed is the summary for all sessions of that application will be returned.
        Returns:
        session state summary map keys by session id. The value of the map is of type SessionState. null is returned if the 'name' is not of type RegistrationType.Application or RegistrationType.Session.

      • sessionStateSummary

        public Map<String,SessionState> sessionStateSummary(Name name,
                                                    Set<Name> relevantSessions)
        Returns a summary of the state of all configured sessions for a given application if 'name' is of type application) or the state of a single session if the type of the 'name' is session. Only sessions contained in the 'relevantSessions' set are returned (can be null for no restrictions)
        Parameters:
        name - Name of top level node to get a summary for. This can be either an Application or Session node. If an Application node is in passed is the summary for all sessions of that application will be returned.
        relevantSessions - A set of sessions to return the state for. If a session is configured but not in that list, its state will not be returned
        Returns:
        session state summary map keys by session id. The value of the map is of type SessionState. null is returned if the 'name' is not of type RegistrationType.Application or RegistrationType.Session.
